TWO people died in a multi-vehicles crash on Thursday morning, on the N1 in Limpopo. The accident reportedly happened on the N1 just before the Bela Bela off ramp. The Limpopo Department of Transport spokesperson Matome Moremi-Taueatsoala said two of theÂ people were the driver and a passenger in the stationary truck. The truck that was transporting cars was badly damaged and the driver injured. Motorists were advised to be cautious and be patient.  